---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
import SectionDivider from '../../components/SectionDivider.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Our Story" description="The founding narrative of the Gregory the Great Institute — from Saskatchewan to Oxford to cultural renewal in Canada.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero-story section--dark">
    <div class="hero-story__bg" style={`background-image: url(${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}images/art/Bodleian-Library-Oxford.jpg)`}></div>
    <div class="hero-story__overlay"></div>
    <div class="hero-story__content container">
      <p class="label text-gold">About the Institute</p>
      <h1 class="display">Our Story</h1>
      <p class="hero-story__subtitle">From Saskatchewan to Oxford to the mission of Catholic cultural renewal in Canada.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Intro with Portrait -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container story-intro reveal">
      <div class="story-intro__image">
        <img src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}images/people/Ryan-Topping-headshot.jpg`} alt="Dr. Ryan N.S. Topping" />
      </div>
      <div class="story-intro__text">
        <p class="label text-gold">Founding Director</p>
        <h2>Dr. Ryan N.S. Topping</h2>
        <p>
          The Gregory the Great Institute was born from a lifetime of study, conversion, and commitment to
          the Catholic intellectual tradition. Its story is inseparable from the journey of its founder.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SectionDivider />

  <!-- Origins & Conversion -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container story-section reveal">
      <p class="label text-gold">Origins</p>
      <h2>A Mennonite Beginning</h2>
      <p>
        Ryan Topping grew up Mennonite in Saskatchewan and British Columbia. Together with his wife Anna, he
        pursued studies in classics, philosophy, and theology — a path that would eventually lead them both
        across the Atlantic.
      </p>
      <p>
        Ryan completed a Master of Arts in philosophy at the University of Manitoba, writing on Plato's
        psychology of the human person. But it was at Oxford that the decisive turn came. While studying
        there, he and Anna attended the funeral of Pope John Paul II — an experience that became the catalyst
        for their conversion to Catholicism.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Oxford -->
  <section class="section section--linen">
    <div class="container story-section reveal">
      <p class="label text-gold">Formation</p>
      <h2>Oxford: Faith and Reason United</h2>
      <p>
        At the University of Oxford, Ryan pursued doctoral studies under an extraordinary constellation of
        mentors: <strong>Oliver O'Donovan</strong>, <strong>Fr. Aidan Nichols OP</strong>, and
        <strong>Sir Roger Scruton</strong>. He earned a Master's in theology focusing on political thought,
        followed by a DPhil on St. Augustine's moral and educational philosophy.
      </p>
      <p>
        Oxford brought other formative encounters. Ryan studied alongside and was influenced by
        <strong>John Finnis</strong>, <strong>Ralph McInerny</strong>, <strong>Fr. John Saward</strong>,
        <strong>Stratford Caldecott</strong>, and <strong>Walter Hooper</strong> — C.S. Lewis' last
        secretary. The family worshipped at the Oxford Oratory, the former parish of Cardinal Newman
        and Gerard Manley Hopkins.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2008, Ryan and Anna returned to North America with their first sons, Peter and Joseph.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Community Work -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container story-section reveal">
      <p class="label text-gold">Community</p>
      <h2>Emmaus House, Winnipeg</h2>
      <p>
        Before Oxford, Ryan and Anna co-founded <strong>Emmaus House</strong>, an intentional Christian
        community in downtown Winnipeg — an early expression of the conviction that faith must take
        institutional and communal form to truly renew culture.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Academic Career -->
  <section class="section section--linen">
    <div class="container story-section reveal">
      <p class="label text-gold">Academic Career</p>
      <h2>Building Catholic Studies Across Canada</h2>
      <p>
        Ryan's academic career carried the family across North America. He taught Catholic Studies at
        <strong>St. Thomas College</strong> in Saskatoon, held the <strong>Chair in Catholic Studies</strong>
        at St. Thomas University in Fredericton, and served as a Fellow at <strong>Thomas More College</strong>
        near Boston.
      </p>
      <p>
        At <strong>Newman Theological College</strong> in Edmonton, Ryan served as Vice-President and
        Academic Dean. During his tenure he solidified accreditation, established the first Bachelor of Arts
        in Catholic Studies, secured over $1 million in outreach funding, published a national study on
        newly ordained priests in Canada, and nearly doubled enrollment.
      </p>
      <p>
        At Newman he also launched a series of initiatives that would become prototypes for the Institute:
        the <strong>Faith and Reason Seminar</strong>, the <strong>John Paul II Leadership Camp</strong>,
        and the <strong>Catholic Culture Internship</strong> program.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Family -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container story-section reveal">
      <p class="label text-gold">Family</p>
      <h2>Rooted in Domestic Life</h2>
      <p>
        Ryan and Anna are the parents of eight children. They are a founding family of
        <strong>Campion Classical Academy</strong> in Alberta, where Anna serves as Administrator.
        Their eldest son is studying as a seminarian — a sign of the fruitfulness of the tradition
        they have laboured to cultivate.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Publications & Honours -->
  <section class="section section--linen">
    <div class="container story-section reveal">
      <p class="label text-gold">Publications & Honours</p>
      <h2>Eleven Books and Counting</h2>
      <p>
        Ryan is the author of <strong>eleven books</strong> on Catholic culture and education. His work has
        appeared in <em>First Things</em>, and he has been featured on <em>EWTN</em>, <em>Word on Fire</em>,
        <em>Crisis Magazine</em>, <em>Catholic World Report</em>, <em>National Catholic Register</em>,
        <em>Shalom Media</em>, and <em>The Epoch Times</em>.
      </p>
      <p>
        In recognition of his contributions, Ryan was awarded the <strong>Queen Elizabeth II Platinum
        Jubilee Medal</strong> by the Province of Alberta.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SectionDivider />

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section" style="text-align: center;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>The Institute Today</h2>
      <p style="max-width: 640px; margin-inline: auto; font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-gray); margin-bottom: 24px;">
        Everything in Ryan's journey — conversion, study, community, institution-building, family — converges
        in the Gregory the Great Institute. It exists to do for others what Oxford, Newman, and those
        communities of faith did for him: form minds and hearts in the light of the Catholic tradition.
      </p>
      <Button href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}about/`} variant="secondary">← Back to About</Button>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .hero-story {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 380px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-story__bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
  }

  .hero-story__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(14, 51, 82, 0.75), rgba(14, 51, 82, 0.85));
  }

  .hero-story__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-block: 60px;
  }

  .hero-story__content h1 {
    color: var(--color-text-on-dark);
    margin: 8px 0 12px;
  }

  .hero-story__subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: rgba(245, 239, 229, 0.85);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Intro */
  .story-intro {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 32px;
    align-items: center;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .story-intro__image img {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 280px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    display: block;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .story-intro__text h2 {
    margin: 8px 0 12px;
  }

  .story-intro__text p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-gray);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .story-intro {
      grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    }
    .story-intro__image img {
      margin-inline: 0;
    }
  }

  /* Story Sections */
  .story-section {
    max-width: 740px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .story-section h2 {
    margin: 8px 0 16px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    color: var(--color-navy);
  }

  .story-section p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-gray);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .story-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .section--linen {
    background-color: var(--color-linen);
  }
</style>
